summary: So I just saw Captain Marvel... again
body:
So I just saw Captain Marvel… again

And honestly I have such a mammoth crush on Brie Larson it’s not even funny.

But seriously, watching it again really made me appreciate even more the underlying messages in the movie that are so relevant today. It was also nice to relive the humour. In my opinion it’s one of the funniest movies in the marvel cinematic universe. It’s just such a great movie and I love it.

Also, I totally ship Maria and Carol. Just saying 🤷🏳️‍🌈🦄

summary: you know what i loved about captain marvel the most?
title: you know what i loved about captain marvel the most?
body:
the bit at the very end, when yon-rugg is demanding that she prove herself by putting a lid on her emotions.

it’s a theme prevalent throughout the movie, and honestly as a woman i never realised just how chastised we are for simply having and expressing emotions. because according to people like yon-rugg, who really does represent a lot of our own society, emotions are weaknesses. women are too ‘emotional’ to lead. emotions lessen our significance, and women and men are both expected to push them aside in order to be strong.

what i LOVED about carol is that she completely flipped this around. her emotions are her strength. as she says to the supreme intelligence, ‘i’ve been fighting with one hand tied behind my back.’ she fights with her heart, for the pain she feels for the persecuted skrulls and for her long-lost now found friends. she fights for her family. her home.

too often in our society, traditional ‘feminine’ values are deemed lesser than supposedly ‘masculine’ ones, such as physical brute strength and stone-hard will. captain marvel shows us that those ‘weaker’ values are actually strong. unstoppable, even. fighting for something, fighting with your emotions, your heart, makes you so much more powerful. carol fights with her heart, powers, combat skills and strength all on the same level, each needed, each necessary.

yon-rugg was training vers to be ‘the best version of herself,’ that most served his and the kree’s purposes. because he knew - he knew that if she unlocked her true potential, if she fought with her emotions rather than locking them away, she’d knock his sorry ass across the galaxy and back. he knew her true strength, painted it as a weakness so she’d be in the dark about her true power forever. another mindless soldier for him to mould. he was afraid of her; he was afraid of her heart.

because her heart is the most powerful weapon carol has; its what saved the skrulls, what decimated those kree warships ten times her size.

you want carol to fight you controlling her emotions? with one hand behind her back?

jokes on you, yon-rugg. she’s free. her heart is free. she decimated a kree fleet and whooped while doing it. she is no longer shackled to you.

she is carol motherfucking danvers, captain marvel. and she doesn’t have to prove herself to anyone but herself.

(idk if this made any sense whatsoever but i fucking loved this movie and no one can convince me otherwise)
